{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The evaluate-stage command stores grounding into a dedicated `grounding` artifact, not the `plan` artifact.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is wiring between evaluate-stage output mapping and artifact persistence. A unit test of a formatter won’t catch misrouted writes in the command-to-store path.","test_description":"Run the real evaluate-stage command handler with a test artifact store. Seed an existing `plan` artifact, execute evaluate, then assert: (a) new content is written to `grounding`, (b) `plan` is unchanged, and (c) artifact metadata records a `grounding` write event.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The implement-stage flow reads grounding when available and still writes its execution output to `plan`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is read/write coordination across implement flow + artifact retrieval + artifact persistence. The real risk is incorrect slot selection at module boundaries, not isolated function logic.","test_description":"With a test store containing both `grounding` and prior artifacts, execute implement flow end-to-end (within process). Assert grounding is loaded into implement context/input and output is persisted only to `plan`, while `grounding` remains intact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Deep-dive no longer overwrites `plan` as a redundant side effect when diagnosis already exists in issue content.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The bug is a conditional side effect in stage orchestration plus artifact store interaction. Unit logic checks can miss that the command still emits a write through integration wiring.","test_description":"Prepare issue content that already includes diagnosis and seed a `plan` artifact. Run deep-dive stage through its normal command path. Assert no write call targets `plan` (or no new `plan` version appears), while deep-dive still completes successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"In a full multi-step agent run (`deep-dive -> write-plan/evaluate -> implement`), the final implementation plan reflects grounding produced earlier in the run.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"The failure appears across stage sequencing and cross-step state handoff in the end-to-end pipeline. Single-step integration tests can pass while multi-step run-order/state propagation still fails.","test_description":"Execute the real three-step pipeline in one run context. Inject a distinctive grounding fact during evaluate, then verify the final `plan` artifact includes that grounding signal and that artifact lineage shows `grounding` created before implement consumes it.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.5}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When grounding is absent, implement falls back safely and still emits a valid plan artifact without corrupting other stored artifacts.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is fallback behavior at the boundary of implement flow and artifact store state. Need real module interaction to ensure missing-read handling and non-corrupting writes.","test_description":"Run implement with no `grounding` artifact but with other unrelated artifacts present. Assert implement succeeds, writes a syntactically valid `plan`, does not create malformed `grounding`, and leaves unrelated artifacts unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_prob